*Questioning test requirements**\\n\\nI’m considering whether generated tests really need to use the Sonatype transformer. The idea of “meaningful coverage” makes me think that it might be necessary for achieving full coverage, especially regarding dynamic access. I want to make sure we're fully testing what we need, but there’s a part of me that's unsure if it's absolutely required or if there's a way to manage without it. It's all about striking that balance, right?\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Evaluating library dependencies**\\n\\nI need to look into the dependencies for the library. The docs mention Maven 3.1.0, but the POM shows an older aether provided. If things aren't deterministic, the agent might get stuck. I could include some specific dependencies like sisu-inject-plexus and aether-api/util, but I’m unsure if they’re truly needed. It's essential to inspect the official documentation or source to see their intended usage, possibly fetching the source-release or using Gradle for more clarity.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_yQTuJW6esRO5XLpsY4jAVo5r|fc_03ce6bd239914f6b016a3eea4408088193b737229075ca260b", "name": "bash", "arguments": {"command": "python3 - <<'PY'\nfrom pathlib import Path\nbase=Path.home()/'.gradle/caches/modules-2/files-2.1/org.apache.maven.shared/maven-common-artifact-filters/3.1.1'\nprint([str(p) for p in base.rglob('*sources*')])\nPY\ncurl -L -s -o /tmp/mcaf-sources.jar https://repo.maven.apache.org/maven2/org/apache/maven/shared/maven-common-artifact-filters/3.1.1/maven-common-artifact-filters-3.1.1-sources.jar && jar tf /tmp/mcaf-sources.jar | rg 'Sonatype|Eclipse|site|xdoc' | head -50", "timeout": 60}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 5725, "output": 970, "cacheRead": 51200, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 57895, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1782508085620, "response