 I also need to consider the use of `maven-resolver-api/util` for extra coverage, even if it's possibly leftover in the POM. Lastly, it’s preferable to utilize Maven 3.1's APIs for establishing project dependencies effectively.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Updating dependencies and guidance**\\n\\nThe guidance can mention APIs, but I can't simply say to \\\"add deps.\\\" For the code, I need to update test imports to `org.eclipse.aether` for `ProjectBuildingResult`. I can test the Sonatype transformer separately using its classes.\\n\\nI need to be cautious about transitive overrides affecting the Sisu version compared to the artifact POM. Existing tests using Sonatype Aether types won’t compile with the later version, so the generator must adapt accordingly. Additionally, I should keep the JSON format deterministic and ensure that the dependencies are managed correctly to avoid unnecessary reachability issues.\"}]}"}, {"type": "text", "text": "{\n  \"action\": \"advisory_preparation\",\n  \"summary\": \"3.1.1 is a Maven Shared component with no Docker or environment needs, but its resolved Gradle graph has a bad old Sisu transitive dependency and its Sonatype Aether transformer uses provided dependencies that the normal scaffold will not receive transitively.\",\n  \"deterministic_setup\": [\n    {\n      \"kind\": \"dependency\",\n      \"coordinate\": \"org.sonatype.sisu:sisu-inject-plexus:2.6.0\",\n      \"scope\": \"testImplementation\",\n      \"reason\": \"Overrides the direct 1.4.2 transitive path whose POM requests the nonexistent org.sonatype.sisu:sisu-guice:3.1.0:noaop artifact during Gradle resolution.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"kind\": \"dependency\",\n      \"coordinate\": \"org.sonatype.aether:aether-api:1.7\",\n      \"scope\": \"testImplementation\",\n      \"reason\": \"The library exposes SonatypeAetherFilterTransformer APIs backed by org.sonatype.aether classes declared as provided in the artifact POM.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"kind\": \"dependency\",\n      \"coordinate\": \"org.sonatype.aether:aether-util:1.7\",\n      \"scope\": \"testImplementation\",\n      \"reason\": \"Needed with aether-api to instantiate and exercise the Sonatype Aether dependency filters exposed by the library.\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"agent_guidance\": \"No Docker image, environment variable, or system property is indicated. For 3.1.1, use Maven 3.1/Eclipse Aether types when implementing Maven ProjectBuildingResult or DependencyResolutionResult test doubles; the old 3.0.0 tests' Sonatype Aether return types no longer match those Maven interfaces. Sonatype Aether coverage should target SonatypeAetherFilterTransformer directly, separate from Maven 3.1 project-building interfaces.\",\n  \"risks\": [\n    \"The Sisu override changes an old transitive dependency version, so Gradle and native-image verification remain authoritative.\",\n    \"Existing 3.0.0 tests are not directly portable because Maven 3.1.0 changed relevant dependency-resolution interfaces to Eclipse Aether types.\"\n  ]\n}", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_03ce6bd239914f6b016a3eea5d0a988193b9cdfa9f8e579c98\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 2037, "output": 995, "cacheRead": 59392, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 62424, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "stop", "timestamp": 1782508113438, "responseId": "resp_03ce6bd239914f6b016a3eea520cfc8193a1431f680b9d28a1"}, "toolResults": []}
